
I laid down next to him making sure to keep an okay distance just incase, but he covered us in the same blanket and pulled me closer. Unexpectedly, his hand wrapped around my waist. Funny how this morning he was yelling at me for being in his bed and now I'm back in it.
"You know, you never answered my question," I playfully huffed. It fell silent. I almost thought he was asleep.
"Yes. I was," he smiled and pecked my cheek. I'm glad he can't see me blushing in the darkness.
I like this new Harry.
